# Typography

Typography is essential for creating clear, readable, and visually appealing interfaces in Bioma.

## Font Family

### Primary Font: Sora

Sora is a geometric sans-serif designed for digital interfaces.

```scss
--font-primary: 'Sora', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
```

**Weights Available**: 300 (Light), 400 (Regular), 500 (Medium), 600 (Semibold), 700 (Bold)

### Monospace Font: SF Mono

For code and technical content:

```scss
--font-mono: 'SF Mono', Monaco, 'Cascadia Code', monospace;
```

## Type Scale

| Token | Size | Usage |
|-------|------|-------|
| --font-xs | 12px | Fine print, captions |
| --font-sm | 14px | Secondary text, labels |
| --font-base | 16px | Body text (default) |
| --font-lg | 18px | Large body text |
| --font-xl | 20px | Subheadings |
| --font-2xl | 24px | Section titles |
| --font-3xl | 30px | Page titles |
| --font-4xl | 36px | Hero headings |
| --font-5xl | 48px | Display headings |

## Font Weights

```scss
--font-light: 300;
--font-regular: 400;
--font-medium: 500;
--font-semibold: 600;
--font-bold: 700;
```

## Line Heights

```scss
--leading-none: 1;
--leading-tight: 1.25;
--leading-snug: 1.375;
--leading-normal: 1.5;
--leading-relaxed: 1.625;
--leading-loose: 2;
```

## Usage

### Headings

```scss
h1 {
  font-size: var(--font-4xl);
  font-weight: var(--font-bold);
  line-height: var(--leading-tight);
  color: var(--text-strong);
}

h2 {
  font-size: var(--font-3xl);
  font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
}
```

### Body Text

```scss
p {
  font-size: var(--font-base);
  font-weight: var(--font-regular);
  line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  color: var(--text-primary);
}
```

